claims:
Claims 1. System (1) for transporting a plurality of tools designed to be transformable into at least one temporary workplace (2) adapted to enable performing a plurality of working jobs in the field of optical fibers through said workplace (2) , said system (1) being equipped with: an external case, composed of a lower portion (3) , and of an upper portion (5) ; at least one bearing element (4) ; two or more multi-function bars (6) ; and four or more supporting elements (8) arranged inside said upper portion (5) of said case during a transport of said system (1) by a user, characterized in that said two or more multi function bars (6) are composed of two or more profiles adapted to delimit a recess adapted to place and fasten said plurality of tools, said two or more multi-function bars (6) being equipped with a plurality of fastening means (18) , adapted to enable an installation of a plurality of accessories, enabling a customization of said workplace (2) by said user; and in that said lower portion (3) is equipped therein with a plurality of dividing means adapted 

 to form three or more areas aimed to house and protect said plurality of tools, wherein the first area (14a) is adapted to house electric components, with visible multi -sockets (16) , the second area (14b) is equipped with removable elements adapted to house optical components and the plurality of tools for working optical fibers, and the third area (14c) is adapted to house a splicer and its accessories, in particular a cutter and a power supply. 2. System (2) according to the previous claim, characterized in that said system (1) further comprises : two or more opening and closing means (9) of said system (1) , equipped with a first element arranged above and/or laterally along said lower portion (3) of said case and of a second element arranged above and/or laterally along said upper portion (5) of the case, adapted to connect said lower portion (3) with said upper portion (5) during said transport of said system (1) by said user, and to enable a separation of said upper portion (5) from said lower portion (3) during a step of transforming said system (1) into said workplace (2) ; 

 at least one transporting element (7a) arranged on said lower portion (3) of said case of said system (1) ; at least one removable transporting element (7b) , arranged on said lower portion (3) of said case of said system (1) ; two or more wheels (11) , arranged below said lower portion (3) of said case of said system (1) ; two or more bearing means (13) , adapted to enable a horizontal positioning of said system (1) conferring greater stability to said workplace (2); and a covering element (15) of said lower portion (3) of said case of said system (1) . 3. System (1) according to claim 1, characterized in that said four or more supporting elements (8) are constrained to said upper portion (5) and to said lower portion (3) of said case of said system (1) , through at least one locking system, enabling a mechanical coupling between said bearing element (4) and said lower portion (3) , conferring stability to said workplace (2) when performing said plurality of working jobs by said user. 4. System (1) according to claim 2, characterized in that said two or more opening and closing means 

 (9) are equipped with at least one fastening element . 5. System (1) according to any one of the previous claims, characterized in that said system (1) is adapted to assume a first configuration adapted to contain therein said plurality of tools and to transport said plurality of tools, and to assume a second configuration being transformed into said workplace (2) . 6. Method for transforming a system (1) according to any one of the previous claims from a first configuration to a second configuration, said method comprising the steps of : providing said system (1) ; - activating said two or more opening and closing means (9) ; separating said upper portion (5) from said lower portion (3) of said case of said system (1) ; inserting said upper and lower ends of each of said four or more supporting elements (8) respectively on said lower surface of said upper portion (5) and on said upper surface of said lower portion (3) ; providing and placing said plurality of tools on said two or more multi-function bars (6) ; 

 activating said workplace (2) ; and possibly placing said plurality of said additional bearing elements (12) .
